kages(&quot;gender&quot;) library(gender) #&gt; PLEASE NOTE: The method provided by this package must be used cautiously #&gt; and responsibly. Please be sure to see the guidelines and warnings about #&gt; usage in the README or the package documentation. Let's do some searches for the name Kelsey. gender(&quot;Kelsey&quot;) #&gt; # A tibble: 1 x 6 #&gt; name proportion_male proportion_female gender year_min year_max #&gt; &lt;chr&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;chr&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; #&gt; 1 Kelsey 0.0314 0.969 female 1932 2012 gender(&quot;Kelsey&quot;, years = 1940) #&gt; # A tibble: 1 x 6 #&gt; name proportion_male proportion_female gender year_min year_max #&gt; &lt;chr&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;chr&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;dbl&gt; #&gt; 1 Kelsey 1 0 male 1940 1940
